AWKA – Critical stakeholders under the aegis of Aguata North Po­litical Forum have endorsed the member representing Aguata II State Constituency in the Anambra State House of Assembly, Hon. Okechuk­wu Okoye, aka Okey di Okay, for a second term in office. Following a consultative meeting held at Igboukwu, Aguata Local Government Area and attended by mem­bers of the Executive of Aguata North Political Fo­rum, traditional rulers and Presidents-General of the eight communities of Aguata II State Constituency, as well as representatives of the 11 wards of the constituency, the forum also appealed to the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) to give it is ticket to Okoye to enable him realise his re-election bid for the greater good of the Agua­ta II Constituency. In a communique issued after the meeting, the group observed that Okoye had performed exceedingly well, especially through many im­pactful constituency projects initiated and completed by him in almost all the